body:
Hi folks, just checking in to say I've seen the PR and will try to get the fix out soon.

> Worst case the crate can be easily forked and we can move it to the Alacritty organization. IIRC there's also been the suggestion to replace this crate and iirc there should even be a code comment in the windows pty somewhere, but that would require someone who's actually interested in working on Windows.

@chrisduerr I'd be very happy to transfer ownership of the crate to the alacritty org, if you want that? As far as I know the crate has no dependents other than alacritty, and I was kinda hoping https://github.com/microsoft/terminal/issues/262 would eventually happen anyway so the crate could be thrown out in favor of a `NamedPipe` implementation like we used to use with winpty.

For the record I'm still a heavy user of alacritty on both Windows and Linux, just it's more than good enough for my daily driver so I haven't had urgency to push changes. Do continue to ping me any time if there's things needed from me! (These days all my OSS free time is devoted to https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3.)

> I am a casual contributor of the Windows Terminal project so I know a bit in this specific area. If there's anything I can help regarding ConPTY & related., I will see what I can do within my power.

@skyline75489 that's really cool! A long time ago I looked into implementing some of the things we wanted upstream, but large Visual Studio projects aren't my strong suit and I gave up trying to get the darn thing to build. If we had an issue tracking the things we wanted from upstream conpty perhaps we can coordinate on them together? As above not sure I'll achieve much but I'm at least somewhat familiar with the current limitations conpty puts on us.
